===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|authorship}} A [[clichéd]] conclusion in which all [[loose end]]s are tied up and all main characters are content. See also [[happily ever after]].
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Bertrand Russell|authorlink=Bertrand Russell|title=The Conquest of Happiness|year=1930|passage=Life is not to be conceived on the analogy of a melodrama in which the hero and heroine go through incredible misfortunes for which they are compensated by a '''happy ending'''.}}
#* {{quote-av|en|actor={{w|Mel Blanc}}|role={{w|Bugs Bunny}}|title=[[w:What's Opera, Doc?|What’s Opera, Doc?]]|date=6 July 1957|passage=Well, what did you expect in an opera? A '''happy ending'''?}}
#* {{quote-song|en|composer={{w|Willy DeVille}}|title=Storybook Love|year=1987|passage=And she said: / "Don't you know that storybook loves, / Always have a '''happy ending'''."}}
# {{lb|en|vulgar|slang|euphemistic}} A [[hand job]], especially one provided by the [[masseuse]] to the [[client]] at or towards the end of a [[massage#Noun|massage]].

